title: Cache write queue can stall if cacheWriter onNewData never fires
updated_at: "2026-07-15T06:55:58Z"
---
## Problem
`enqueueCacheWrite` sets `_cacheWriteBusy = true` then `cacheWriter.connectSource(...)`. The queue only drains in `cacheWriter.onNewData`. If the executable engine fails to emit `onNewData` (bad source, engine hang, process never started), `_cacheWriteBusy` stays true and all subsequent response caches are silently dropped for the session.

## Location
`contents/ui/ProfileController.qml` — `drainCacheWriteQueue`, `cacheWriter` DataSource

## Suggested fix
Add a Timer watchdog that resets `_cacheWriteBusy` and retries/drains after N seconds; or use one-shot DataSource per write without a global busy flag; or call `drainCacheWriteQueue` from a periodic timer when queue non-empty and busy stuck.

## Source
Post-merge static review of response-cache queue